<title type="html"><![CDATA[SNSRAM]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1002&amp;p=8706#p8706"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">pragma wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />In the meantime, I'd like to have something <em>real</em> to develop against but w/o the added turnaound time of reprogramming a fpga *and* roms.<br /></div><br />Get yourself an SNROM board (common as dirt: Metroid, Zelda, etc), rewire it for whatever ROMs you prefer, and modify it to read a PRG and CHR segment of up to 8 KB each from the controller port. Then run a cable to your PC's parallel port and send the program that way.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Jan 27, 2006 7:11 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
